<p><strong><span style="color:#ff5555">Introduction</span></strong></p>

<hr />

<p>Writable /etc/shadow file can also be used to Escalate Privileges in linux. As we seen in previous post (<a href="https://www.codeh4ck3r.xyz/posts/weak-file-permissions-1/">Readable /etc/shadow</a>) We were able to read content of /etc/shadow file and with that permission we took hash and cracked it using john.
In this Privilege Escalation technique we are going to replace old hash of root user with new hash in /etc/shadow file.
And then we are going to login as root.</p>

